Finland's gross national product isexpected to rise by three pct in 1987 against two pct in 1986and inflation will be unchanged at about 3.5 pct, the privatebusiness survey office ETLA predicted.    Unemployment in 1987 is put at 5.5 pct, in line with lastyear, the office predicted in its regular review.    The balance of payments would show a five billion markkadeficit in 1987, against a 4.2 billion deficit in 1986. REUTER&#3;